mainmatter.p:
Let { M } \xrightarrow {{ \Phi , \Psi }}{ N } be two (lax) homomorphisms from M to N. A transformation { \Phi } \xrightarrow {{ \alpha }}{ \Psi } of homomorphisms from M to N is by three cells






  \usepackage {string-diagrams,preamble}


     \begin {tikzpicture}[scale=0.5,baseline=($(nw)!0.5!(se)$)]
       \CreateRect { 3 }{ 2 }
       \path 
        coordinate[label=above:$ \strut \Phi _{ E } $] (n) at (spath cs:north 0.5)
        coordinate[label=below:$ \strut \Psi _{ E } $] (s) at (spath cs:south 0.5)
      ;
       \draw [spath/save=vert] (n) to (s);
       \path  coordinate[dot,label=left:$ \alpha _{ E } $] (cell) at (spath cs:vert 0.5);
       \begin {scope}[on background layer]
         \fill [ catd ] (nw) rectangle (s);
         \fill [ cate ] (n) rectangle (se);
       \end {scope}
     \end {tikzpicture}

   \quad 

     \begin {tikzpicture}[scale=0.5,baseline=($(nw)!0.5!(se)$)]
       \CreateRect { 3 }{ 2 }
       \path 
        coordinate[label=above:$ \strut \Phi _{ U } $] (n) at (spath cs:north 0.5)
        coordinate[label=below:$ \strut \Psi _{ U } $] (s) at (spath cs:south 0.5)
      ;
       \draw [spath/save=vert] (n) to (s);
       \path  coordinate[dot,label=left:$ \alpha _{ U } $] (cell) at (spath cs:vert 0.5);
       \begin {scope}[on background layer]
         \fill [ catc ] (nw) rectangle (s);
         \fill [ violet!40 ] (n) rectangle (se);
       \end {scope}
     \end {tikzpicture}

   \quad 

     \begin {tikzpicture}[scale=0.5,baseline=($(nw)!0.5!(se)$)]
       \CreateRect { 3 }{ 2 }
       \path 
        coordinate[label=above:$ \strut \Phi _{ \mathcal {C} } $] (n) at (spath cs:north 0.5)
        coordinate[label=below:$ \strut \Psi _{ \mathcal {C} } $] (s) at (spath cs:south 0.5)
      ;
       \draw [spath/save=vert] (n) to (s);
       \path  coordinate[dot,label=left:$ \alpha _{ \mathcal {C} } $] (cell) at (spath cs:vert 0.5);
       \begin {scope}[on background layer]
         \fill [ catf ] (nw) rectangle (s);
         \fill [ brown!40 ] (n) rectangle (se);
       \end {scope}
     \end {tikzpicture}






such that commute with the components of \Phi and \Psi in the following sense:






  \usepackage {string-diagrams,preamble}




     \begin {tikzpicture}[scale=0.5,baseline=($(nw)!0.5!(se)$)]
       \CreateRect { 5 }{ 4 }
       \path 
        coordinate[label=above:$ \strut \Phi _{ E } $] (f0) at (spath cs:north 0.5)
        coordinate[label=above:$ \strut p _{ N } $] (lB) at (spath cs:north 0.75)
        coordinate[label=below:$ \strut p _{ M } $] (lA) at (spath cs:south 0.25)
        coordinate[label=below:$ \strut \Psi _{ U } $] (f1) at (spath cs:south 0.5)
      ;
       \draw [spath/save = f01] (f0) to (f1);
       \draw [spath/save = lBA] (lB) to[out=-90,in=90] (lA);
       \path [name intersections={of=f01 and lBA}]
        coordinate[dot, 
    label=-10:$ \Psi _{ p } $
   ] (lambda) at (intersection-1)
      ;

       \path  coordinate[dot,label=left:$ \alpha _E $] (transf) at (spath cs:f01 0.25);

       \begin {scope}[on background layer]
         \fill [ catd ] (nw) rectangle (se);
         \tikzset {
          spath/split at intersections={f01}{lBA},
          spath/get components of={lBA} \lcpts ,
        }
         \fill [ cate ] (lB) to[spath/use={ \getComponentOf \lcpts1 ,weld}] (lambda.center) to (f0) to cycle;
         \fill [ catc ] (lambda.center) to[spath/use={ \getComponentOf \lcpts2 ,weld}] (lA) to (f1) to cycle;
         \fill [ violet!40 ] (lB) to[spath/use={ \getComponentOf \lcpts1 ,weld}] (lambda.center) to (f1) to (se) to (ne) to cycle;
       \end {scope}
     \end {tikzpicture}


